                <head>No. 407.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Langston</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-07-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 6, 1881</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 156.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 389 of the 18th ultimo,
                    touching the probable repeal of the law fixing a tax of one per cent. for
                    consular visas. The information contained in Mr. Laforestrie’s private note to
                    you of the 15th June is acceptable, and I trust that the wise resolution of the
                    Haytian Government to procure the abolition of this obnoxious tax will be
                    speedily accomplished.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
